  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2018-11-14",
    "date": "2018-11-26T17:13:05Z",
    "text": "This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to make permanent the reduction in the adjusted gross income threshold that must be exceeded before a taxpayer is allowed to claim an itemized deduction for medical expenses. (In 2017, the threshold was temporarily reduced from 10% to 7.5% for 2017 and 2018. This bill makes the 7.5% threshold permanent.)"
